title: Wild Assassins
subTitle: Explores the lives of the airborne assassins, Falcons and Eagles, which hunts their preys with their powerful beaks.

title: Cheetah Blood Brothers
subTitle: Strong and fast, cheetahs are one of the savanna's leading predators. However, their lives are not without peril. Follow several groups of cheetahs to discover how they survive in the wilds of Africa.

title: Parenthood
subTitle: A journey like no other - full of moments of joy and danger. For animal parents in the wild, the stakes could not be higher, with success ensuring the future of life on our planet.

title: Africa's Trees of Life
subTitle: Explore the importance of the marula tree in sub-Saharan Africa's ecosystem and the vital role it plays in providing sustenance and sanctuary for local animals.

title: The Lions Rule
subTitle: During the dry season in Ruaha state, a herd of elephants visit the water body at Glade to extract the cleanest water using their trunks.

title: Cheetah: Against All Odds
subTitle: Follows 2 families of cheetahs struggle against heat, starvation and predators on the Serengeti.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: The seven teenage lions of the Nsefu pride are training to become hunters, but their misbehaviour has created challenges for the otherwise seemingly flawless group.

title: Wild Africa: Rivers of Life
subTitle: On the Luangwa River, the law of the land is dictated by the ever-changing seasons and the constant cycle of life. In the wet season the Luangwa Valley is a green paradise, as the waters flow in abundance and lush green vegetation carpets the landscape. But in the dry season, when rains become but a distant memory, the greenery turns brown and the water levels drop by a foot per day.

title: Islands: Nature's Wild Laboratories
subTitle: Journey to the largest island in the Canadian Arctic and encounter Arctic foxes, white beluga whales, a never-before-filmed two-tusked narwhal, and other remarkable animals.

title: Tiger Legacy
subTitle: The crew look at the various challenges mothers of different species face in order to keep their cubs alive.

title: Wildest Survival
subTitle: Animals living in extremes have created ingenious tools and techniques to cope with survival's harshest challenges.

title: The Leopardess
subTitle: The Serengeti and its labyrinth of gallery forests are the home of a leopardess. To her family she is both caring provider and fearless defender. For her prey she is sudden death, for her son the only chance to survive in this unforgiving wilderness.

title: Epic Animal Encounters
subTitle: When a male leopard stumbles upon the scene of another leopard making a kill, he leaps in to assist instead of chasing off the other leopard and potentially losing the prey.

title: Jungle Planet
subTitle: The Taiga, the world's largest forest, occupies the northern regions of North America, Europe and Asia and is inhabited by bears, wolverines, wolves and moose.

title: Africa's Hunters
subTitle: Kamuti is a wise old leopard who has reigned over two square miles of prime territory in the Luangwa Valley for ten years, but now she is in trouble. At 13-years-old, Kamuti is one of the oldest leopards in the African bush, and she is not as effective a hunter as she used to be. Kamuti's problems are compounded by her neighbours, the Nsefu pride of lions, who steal her kills and attack her on sight.

title: Race of Life
subTitle: There are many fine examples of evolutionary history in the natural world. Animals adapt through a series of small, random mutations and usually do so in order to compete more effectively for food, water and space. Crocodiles are certainly of an ancient lineage, they are believed to be 200 million years old. Sharks have gone through the process of adaptation and evolutionary experimentation as well.

title: Wild Africa: Rivers of Life
subTitle: For four months of the year, the powerful Limpopo river revitalises the landscape, nourishing the abundance of wildlife dependent on it. For the remaining seven months its waters are locked away in inaccessible underground aquifers, leaving behind a series of small and ever-shrinking muddy pools. Excruciating heat and drought ravage the area until the next rains.
